<paragraph blockId="110.[189,1399,1532,1742]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,401,1576,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,401,1576,1601]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Mesoconius nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[409,500,1575,1601]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to, and obviously closely related to, 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1053,1235,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1053,1235,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">M. quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1243,1334,1575,1601]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[189,247,1610,1636]" name="Peru" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Peru</collectingCountry>
. These species share the four spermathecae, limited constriction at the abdominal base, narrowed T3–5, and similar colour and general habitus, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[770,872,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[770,872,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[879,969,1646,1672]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1122,1302,1645,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1122,1302,1645,1671]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">M. quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1309,1399,1646,1672]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having well-developed vertical and postocellar bristles. 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[865,1102,1680,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[865,1102,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Mesoconius ruficrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1108,1198,1681,1707]" pageId="110" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1266,1320,1681,1707]" name="Peru" pageId="110" pageNumber="111">Peru</collectingCountry>
is also very similar, but differs in colour. All three species share a setose prosternum.
</paragraph>
